                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm irked as it is today, so this is just a l'il post to let off some steam. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
I was in a BoT group the other night, and it was one of the better ones I've been in. The monk was pulling without a problem, the paladin was tanking without a problem (a bit slow stunning on inc, but not too bad), I wasn't getting many resists, and everything was going smoothly. Even got two named mobs to pop in a row at msr. All in all, a good group.
<br />

<br />
So the mage decides to leave and we invite a wizard to take his place. Joins the group and asks for a KEI. We have a mob incoming, so I slow him and then start casting KEI. Of course, 5 seconds into the cast we have a pop that adds. No prob, because the mob we're fighting is at 40 percent health and the tank has been freshly healed. So (and I probably made a mistake here) I finish up the cast of kei before taking care of the add.
<br />

<br />
Mez lands without a problem ... only to be broken a half second later by the main tank. In a panic, I look at the group say spam and see half way up the screen the pally saying "Switch targets."
<br />

<br />
SWITCH TARGETS!!!
<br />

<br />
The mob you're fighting is now at 35% health. He'll be dead shortly. You have an enchanter ... so why why WHY are you switching targets???
<br />

<br />
This is a huge pet peeve for me, and all that it entails. I am the enchanter - I call for the mob we kill and the mob we mez. I equally hate when you have 2 mobs incoming and the tank decides which to attack.
<br />

<br />
No no no. I'm the damn enchanter. I know which one might be resistant to mez, which one might be unrootable, which one is a caster that can be tapped for mana, etc. I DESPISE when tanks make the decision which mob to attack. I have enough friggin' trouble targetting two mobs that are stacked one on top of the other. Let me mez one, then you take the other one.
<br />

<br />
Again, WHY would you even want to switch mobs? Kill the one that's almost dead. It'll be down in 20 seconds anyway, and you can start on this one.
<br />

<br />
On top of that, what's up with the message "switch targets". WTF type of message is that for something so imporant? "ASSIST ME NOW ON &lt;&lt; %t &gt;&gt; OR I'LL KILL YOU!" Now that's a switch mobs message. Not this pansy ass "switch targets" message that half the people in the group didn't notice anyway.
<br />

<br />
So we had 2 mob, and half the group was fighting one, and half the group fighting the other. I wasn't in charm mode, so I didn't have it up to take control of one of the mobs. Lesson learned I guess.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_mad.gif" alt="icon_mad.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
