                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">As much as I would like to control every aspect of my group, what I like to do is keep my /assist on the MT (the joys of a paladin puller) and mez everything MT doesn't target after (or preferably during) the pull.  Then all anybody in the group has to do is keep assisting the MT.  As long as the MT is a good boy or girl and doesn't switch targets, at least not without announcing clearly, then we are good in the hood.  I may not always get to mez the one I think is the ideal mez target, but it is servicable.  Of course, when it comes to choosing witch mezzed mob to attack, they better start listening to me!
