                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I work with a Warrior that can get taunt off of pretty much anything.  He's very much into which gear he wears depending on what his job is.  He's been studying for some time which weapons to use in his "taunt kit".  Since we switched to me pulling in LDoN, with him by my side, and Ykina (our cleric) at my back, not to mention several others that back us up, we've not failed an adventure.
<br />

<br />
Now, as for who picks the targets?  I leave that to the MA.  Why?  I want the MA and the DPS following him ON TARGET NOW.  I don't want any hesitation, I don't want any "are you sure this is the target" I want him to choose a target and do what he does best: kill it.  I don't bother with assist, I just mez a target, if he wakes that target, I mutter under my breath and mez the rest of them.  The only request I've made of him is do save the casters for last so I can mana-tap them... especially the enchanters, as a solo enchanter is wimpy, an enchanter mob with assistance is lethal.
<br />

<br />
To this end I have several messages chained to spells:
<br />

<br />
Dazzle hotkey: announces which target I'm putting to sleep.  My MA will normally steer clear of this target if he can.  If he's already on that target and charging away, then so be it.
<br />

<br />
Apathy hotkey: announces the target as a high priority, do this one next.  The MA knows to finish the current target, and do this one next as it costs extra mana for me to keep it asleep.
<br />

<br />
Can't Mez hotkey: is a very loud obnoxious hotkey telling the group, and raid, and MA (multiple times) that I can't mez this bugger, switch and take it down NOW!  I'll deal with what you are on currently (which can be messy in the case of dots, but, I'll deal with it).
<br />

<br />
I pull with mez.  Apathy if I must.  That way I rarely get multiples on a pull.  If I'm feeling confident, I pull with slow, that way when the critter is in my face, it is rarely able to beat me very hard at all.
<br />

<br />
If the MA switches out of the blue, we usually start talking in tells.... oddly, it's rarely the case where he's made a bad decision when I step back and look at the situation... by the same token, I have him well trained and it's scary how well we work together (though, his instincts are still to take down the casters too early).</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />GnarliAnna
<br />
63 Enchanter of Silent Watchers
<br />
Cazic-Thule</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
