                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I think the main problem is I'm an old time enchanter. Level 64 now (recently returned after an extended hiatus - mainly playing other characters), with hardly any time spent in PoP zones. I guess I'm in the mindset of cluster f*** zones like Chardok, where the adds keep a comin', or Lower Guk before mudflation made it trivial, or the crypt area of Sebilis, where you really really didn't want to wipe out. In those places, I was the one who decided who to attack next. I was the one who took the 7 frog train and turned it into a duck shoot.
<br />

<br />
But I guess PoP really is a different game. Even with 4k hit points, a chanter is going down in a hurry on a 500 plus point double hitter.
<br />

<br />
Doesn't mean I have to like it. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Guess I'll have to get used to letting the main tank lead. Assist tank, get the other mob targetted, mez him.
<br />

<br />
Still friggin' annoying to have the MT switch targets in the middle of a fight. I'm pretty sure most enchanters instincts when they see a mob is "MEZ NOW!" That was the thing I always took the most 'pride' in - being able to see the mob, react, and mez it before anybody else did. I used to love having the mob already mezzed before people noticed it and started calling the add in group. "Yup, already got him locked." <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="icon_biggrin.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
So to have someone switch targets to the add goes against my instincts as an enchanter.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
