                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Making the MT wait until you have locked down all but one mob is horribly inefficient, and will also often lead to your death on a resist, as you will be carrying the bulk of the aggro, and will get multiple mobs on your ass. Let the MT call the target, and if he chooses the blatantly wrong mob (ie, the mezzable instead of the unmezzable) simply call for him to change. In the long run, this will save you time and deaths, unless your tanks suck.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=2212" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.elerion.net/pics/sjhosig.jpg" border="0" /></a><span style="font-style: italic"><span style="font-size: 9px; line-height: normal">
<br />
"Carrot Cake Soup is like the taste of watching girls make out. It has an extraordinary power that oscillates between gentle and overwhelming, between light and dark, between pleasure and more pleasure." - Penny Arcade</span></span></center></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
