                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Personally Im quite happy for chanters to call which mobs to attack next aslong as they call it before the current mob dies.  Once I have my new target I generally dont switch because you can be sure that other melee in your group have already assisted and getting them to assist again is only going to cause confusion.
<br />

<br />
The other side of it is that most guides on "how to be a good tank" and that kinda thing include knowing which mobs are resistant, what order to kill them, what mobs are and aren't mezzable and which to attack first on multi-pulls, so while its generally the tanks job to choose the target, a good tank should know what mobs are mezzable / resistant / not mezzable and choose well accordingly.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-size: 9px; line-height: normal"><span style="font-weight: bold"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=50585" target="_blank" class="postlink">Eoden</a></span> - Half Elf Overlord
