                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The main assist should call the target out, and people should assist him.  I agree with this 100%.
<br />

<br />
What totally irritates me is when a main assist calls a target, people assist him, and then one of the adds jumps me or the healer, and the main assist calls "switch target" again.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">That</span> is annoying as hell, because:
<br />

<br />
(1) The target he switched too is likely (a) unslowed, (b) still pissed off at me or the healer, and (c) was about to be mezzed (or was mezzed, and he broke the mez by switching)
<br />

<br />
(2) The target he switched from (a) may not yet be slowed because I was mezzing the adds and (b) may be unmezzable because of DoTs.
<br />

<br />
This is what I call the "stupid hero" syndrome and is a result of someone who doesn't group with crowd control often.  This happens quite a lot, because there are only two, maybe three, bona fide crowd control classes (Bard and Enchanter, maybe Necromancer), and all of these classes are quite capable of soloing.
<br />

<br />
No one else, as far as I can tell from the pickup groups I have done in the past several weeks, has bothered learning how to root park with the only exception being an occasional skilled Cleric or Shaman.  All the classes you would expect to know how to root park (hybrids who can root) don't know jack about it.  As a former Ranger who nows play an Enchanter and has a Paladin alt, I can't tell you how disappointed I am with the current crop of hybrids.
<br />

<br />
It used to bother me when someone would try to root park while I was playing a crowd control class (Bard or Enchanter), but now I figure, "hey, at least they're trying."  I politely tell them that I can handle the adds, and they're usually very cool about letting me do my job.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=824212" target="_blank" class="postlink">Provender Moonshadow</a>, High Elf Phantasmist
<br />
<a href="http://www.therunes.net/forums/viewtopic.php?p=18979" target="_blank" class="postlink">E61/TT h+ 1.5khp 3.2km ft1 G&lt;3 e+ o++ T+++ L H++ !f g+ b c+++ !t D-- !X</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
