                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">My paladin is my main character (57) though I'm pondering switching as my enchanter is 47 and I really love to play her.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, as a paladin getting up in levels, the mobs are resisting pacify more and more.  Sometimes the enchanters will do the pacifying and tell me which to pull first.  That works for me.  Usually I pacify and pull/call the highest mob I targeted if they con differently, or I'll pull/call a known caster or one that I know hits darn hard.  This usually works since those are the ones I want pulled as an enchanter.  I'm not sure if that's typical or not, but I like to get the hard ones (and almost dead ones) out of the way first.  And I never switch targets; that drives me insane as well.  Especially when another tank in the group decides he/she can "take him on alone"...or the mob was mezzed and the other tank doesn't TAUNT first!  Grrr.  Usually whichever character of the two I'm playing, I tend to be bossy as I hate haphazard pullers.  With the preponderance of real new players (as opposed to those who, like me, leveled up both characters during hell level days), there are MANY people who do not know how to group with enchanters or even casters properly.  Pullers who don't ask for mana check drive me nuts too.
<br />

<br />
My 2 cp.
<br />

<br />
-Galene O'Mana, 47 Enchanter of Drinal
