                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Since grouping with our SK in LDoN I just started to mez when more than 3 mobs are there.
<br />
It's not worth mezzing before, since the SK directly dots and agros 3 mobs so that all hit on her.
<br />
Admitingly she has all her AA and 3 angry mobs hitting her doesn't lower her HP too much.
<br />
Mezzing all adds was what I tried in the beginning, now I just mez when more than 3 or if 2 healers and more.
<br />
This saved me from loosing my nerves and the SK of being angry that I try to mez all adds (Hey she's melee, don't try to argue).
<br />

<br />
But now that GoD is out I am happy since due to the hard hits, they all nicely assist and I can mezz all adds <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
So basically what I learned was, let the tank offtank as many as he wants and adapt to it. 
<br />
They normally know how many they can offtank at the same time.
<br />
If they can't, they will die and learn fast (And after death you can still mez <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /> )
<br />

<br />

<br />
my 2 cp</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Iueamil
