                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Chanters can only control the group to the extent that the group allows them to.  You have to adjust your playstyle depending on the strength of the mobs versus the ability of the tank and also learn the habits of the MT.  Use tells if you are unsure why he did something so you can better understand how to work WITH HIM on future reoccurences.  You don't use the same strategies for every zone/mob in the game.  I've done LDON's where we didn't mez adds at all.  
<br />

<br />
So yeah, we play enchanter because we like controlling the flow of combat, but that is not to say that we should always control the flow of combat.
<br />

<br />
Next time, /tell MT why are you switching? These mez easily.
<br />

<br />
If his answer is, because the pally said to.... then ask him not to do it anymore.  If he continues to do it, quit mezzing and find something else to do.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
