                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">If your tank is calling targets then you shouldnt assist the tank until the target is called.  The best example for why this is is on raids where your tank will be choosing particular targets to attack, say there are 2 mobs in camp one mezzed and one not mezzed the tank will want to attack the not mezzed one, but if they are close together it might take a second or 2 for the tank to get the correct target.  If people assist before the target is called then they'll end up breaking the mezzed one which wont have a tank taunting it.
<br />

<br />
Same deal in XP groups, if the tank is pulling they might target one mob and have another agro which they hadnt seen.  They saw the mob emote so they know that have agro and they run back to camp, but they havent actually seen the mob to target yet.
<br />

<br />
Some tanks will call their target and that makes it a bit easier for you to know when to assist, others don't in which case you need to pay attention to whats going on and play accordingly, with target circles theres really no excuse for sending your pet against a mob that isnt in camp, its just sloppy.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-size: 9px; line-height: normal"><span style="font-weight: bold"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=50585" target="_blank" class="postlink">Eoden</a></span> - Half Elf Overlord
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=215877" target="_blank" class="postlink">Suede</a></span> - Teir Dal Coercer
<br />
Aurora Noctum
<br />
The Tribunal</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
