<br />
   Expect to be driven nuts then.  In my experience, the vast majority of high level pullers will never ask for a mana check.  Rather, it is the responsibility of the casters to tell the puller to stop pulling if they're running low on mana.  The real reason behind this is speed: if the puller has to wait on every pull for the casters to say 'ok', the group will drag.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
